64. __str__
The __str__ method defines what should be displayed when an object is printed using print().
The __str__ method in Python is a special magic (dunder) method used to define a human-readable, user-friendly string representation of a custom class object.Default B

class Book:
    def __init__(self, title, author):
        self.title = title
        self.author = author

my_book = Book("1984", "George Orwell")
print(my_book)  # Output: <__main__.Book object at 0x7f9b18bc3fd0>

    def __init__(self, title, author):
        self.title = title
        self.author = author

    def __str__(self):
        return f"'{self.title}' by {self.author}"

my_book = Book("1984", "George Orwell")
print(my_book)  # Output: '1984' by George Orwell

65. Shallow vs deep copy
